      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(msteams): keep truncated parent context text well-formed",
        "body": "## Problem\n`summarizeParentMessage` truncates the parent body with `text.slice(0, PARENT_TEXT_MAX_CHARS - 1)`. When the cut lands inside a surrogate pair (e.g. an emoji at the boundary), it emits a lone surrogate into the injected `Replying to @sender: …` system event, producing a non-well-formed string.\n\n## Fix\nUse the shared `truncateUtf16Safe` helper (already used by other plugins via `openclaw/plugin-sdk/text-utility-runtime`) so truncation falls back to a whole code-point boundary.\n\n## Proof\nAdded a regression in `extensions/msteams/src/thread-parent-context.test.ts` asserting `summary.text.isWellFormed()` when the limit lands inside an emoji — fails before the fix, passes after. Pure unit test, no live account/network.\n",
